  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0f3a2c8c7b8f4d9c9d5a3d11d5f50101, type: 3}
  m_Name: PokedexSparrow
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entryId: bird_sparrow
  commonName: House Sparrow
  scientificName: Passer domesticus
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: dfd57f2859429594db9442c768ce7e8b, type: 3}
  category: Bird
  habitat: Forest Openings & Fields
  height: 14 - 18 cm
  weight: 24 - 40 g
  diet: Omnivore
  rarity: Very common
  shortDescription: A small, chunky, and highly adaptable bird with a patterned brown,
    gray, and black plumage.
  behaviorNotes: Very social and almost always found in flocks. Flits along the ground
    and dust-baths collectively.
  observationTips: Look near low hedges or forest floors where they chirp loudly
    together in groups.
  funFact: They engage in social dust-bathing, throwing dry dirt over their feathers
    to clean themselves and keep parasites away.
  facts:
  - They are aggressive competitors for nesting sites, sometimes evicting larger
    native birds from established birdhouses.
  - Sparrows prefer to stay incredibly close to ground human activity, rarely nesting
    deep within untouched wilderness areas.
  - They are highly social dust-bathers, gathering in small dirt depressions to throw
    soil over their feathers to stay clean.
